        <name>Meijer $1500 Sign On Bonus!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[🔴 Key Requirements<br>• Must have personal transportation to & from the DC daily<br>• Must be available for nights, weekends, and holidays.<br><br>🔴 Job Details<br>• Training Time: New hires will have a 1 day ride along for $100<br>• Home Time: Daily with 2 days off per week<br>• Freight: Dry & refrigerated. No touch Freight. Mix of live unload and drop & hook.<br>• Running area: Delivering to Meijer locations in OH, KY, and IN (within 250 miles of the DC)<br>• Mileage: 1600-1700 weekly<br>• Tractors: Slip seat. Newer model day cabs. Assigned trucks are only on an as needed basis<br>• Schedule: Start times vary as this is a 24/7 account. Reach out to Kristy Long or Driver Placement to find out what shifts are available. Nights, weekends, and holidays are required. Shifts average 12 hours per day. Full & Part Time shifts available<br>• Flexible Part Time Option: Part-time drivers can work 8-36 hours per week but are not eligible for vacation pay. Please reach out to Kristy Long & Driver Placement if you book a part time driver.<br><br>🔴 Pay<br>• Average weekly: $1350, with potential to earn more<br>• Additional Pay: $51.50 per backhaul. $20 per stop after the first stop. $75 holiday pay. $45 minimum pay for lesser mileage routes (under 96 miles)<br><br>CPM Structure: Experienced Based Pay<br>0-5 months: $0.57/mile<br>6-11 months: $0.58/mile<br>12-23 months: $0.59/mile<br>24-35 months: $0.60/mile<br>36-47 months: $0.61/mile<br>48-59 months: $0.62/mile<br>60-71 months: $0.63/mile<br><br>🔴 Benefits<br>• Consistent daily routes allow drivers to be home every day<br>• Support staff on site 24/7 at the DC to assist<br>• Paid Vacation:<br>o 1 week of vacation after 1 year.<br>o 2 weeks after 3 years.<br>o 3 weeks after 7 years.<br>o 4 weeks after 15 years                                                                        <br>🔴 Sign On Bonus Payout<br>$1500 Total Payout<br>1st Load $ 250<br>30 days $ 500<br>60 days $ 250<br>90 days $ 500    