      <Placemark>
        <name>OTR COMPANY DRIVERS ONLY. CHICAGO BASED. 28 Out 5 home!!(IL, WI, MN, ND, SD, IA, MO, KS, NE) $2000 SIGN ON BONUS!!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[🔴 Job Details<br>• $2000 Sign On Bonus<br>• Home Time: Our drivers typically run 28 days out with 5 days home, giving you the balance between maximizing your earnings and getting the time off you need.<br>• Freight: 100% no-touch freight, with 50-60% drop & hook and 40-50% live unload. No Forced NYC Dispatch: You won’t be required to go into NYC or its five boroughs.<br>• Mileage: On average, drivers typically run around 2,000 miles per week, though this can vary depending on Hours of Service (HOS) and overall availability. Our top performers—about 30% of our fleet—consistently run between 2,300-3,000+ miles per week. Average LOH is 400 miles<br>• Running Area: Covering all 48 states, with most freight running east of I-35—but we go where the freight takes us. We have a suggestive dispatch. Loads are recommended with your area’s freight and your best financial and safety interests in mind<br>• Tractors: Drive in 2021 or newer Freightliner Cascadias or Kenworths.<br><br>🔴 Pay<br>• Additional Pay: $12.50 per hour detention pay after the second hour unless a higher amount is required by state or local law. $100 layover/breakdown pay per day unless a higher amount is required by state or local law.<br>• Performance Bonus: Earn up to an additional 3 CPM based on safety, mileage, and productivity, starting the first of the month following your hire date. Must be an active OTR driver at the time of bonus payout to qualify.<br>• Top 20% of our OTR Drivers at the Chicago Terminal earn $1650 Weekly                                                                ________________________________________<br>For full pay details, click here: Pay Scale https://tinyurl.com/3fe73c78<br><br>*Tagging*<br>Orientation Site: CHICAGO USX Terminal<br>Job: First Seat Driver<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: OTR<br>Acct: OTR<br>Region: 28/5<br>Dedicated Domicile: CHICAGO USX Terminal<br>South Florida: Y/N<br>Company: US Xpress 01 ]]></description>
