        <name>I-35 Fleet. Home Bi-weekly! Regional freight! Need 10 drivers!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Fleet Coverage:<br>Run along the I-35 corridor through Texas, Oklahoma, and Kansas, with a mix of lanes that keep you moving and earning.<br>Home Time:<br>• 2 weeks out / 2 days home — predictable bi-weekly home time while maintaining consistent miles.<br>________________________________________<br>Why You’ll Love It<br>• I-35-focused running area — stay in familiar central-corridor freight lanes<br>• Steady 1800–2000 miles per week<br>• $1000–$1300 weekly average<br>• No-touch freight so you can focus on driving<br>• Straightforward schedule that balances dependable earnings with real downtime<br>Job Details<br>• Average Weekly Miles: 1800-2000<br>• Average Weekly Pay: $1,000–$1,300 gross<br>• Average Length of Haul: 300 miles<br>• Freight: 100% no-touch<br>– 50–60% drop & hook<br>– 40–50% live unload<br>________________________________________<br>Equipment & Support<br>• 2021+ Freightliner Cascadias or Kenworths<br>• 24/7 operations support<br>________________________________________<br>Vacation Package<br>• 1 year = 1 week<br>• 3 years = 2 weeks<br>• 7 years = 3 weeks<br>• 15 years = 4 weeks<br>________________________________________<br>Pay & Bonuses<br>https://tinyurl.com/3fe73c78<br><br>• Detention: $12.50/hr after 2 hrs<br>• Layover/Breakdown: $100/day<br><br>• Performance Bonus: Earn up to an additional 3 CPM based on safety, mileage, and productivity, starting the first of the month following your hire date. Must be an active OTR driver at the time of bonus payout to qualify.<br>Bonus eligibility requirements: o Nothing in this Performance Bonus changes the at-will nature of your employment, meaning you and U.S. Xpress may terminate the employment relationship at any time, with or without cause. o You must be an active company driver on the day the bonus is paid.<br><br>*Tagging*<br>Orientation Site: Dallas<br>Job: First Seat Driver<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: OTR<br>Acct: OTR<br>Region: I-35 Fleet<br>Dedicated Domicile: Dallas