      <Placemark>
        <name>Target Denton Team</name>
        <description><![CDATA[🔴 Key Requirements<br>• Willingness to work a flexible schedule including nights, weekends, and holidays.<br>• Strong customer service mindset and patience in dealing with store personnel.<br>• Ability to manage physically demanding schedules and safety protocols.<br>• Pallets may collapse in transit — securement and care required.<br><br><br>🔴 Job Details<br>• Training: 1 day in the classroom and 1 day ride along at $100/day<br>• Home Time Options:<br>o 6 days on / 1 day off<br>o 12 days on / 2 days off<br>o 25 days on / 3 days off<br>• Freight: Refrigerated, 100% no-touch freight, live unloaded at Target stores. Stops: 1–5 stops per day; Average 6 loads weekly<br>• Mileage: 4,500 average weekly miles.<br>• Running Area: Texas, Arkansas, and Memphis, Tennessee.<br>• Schedule: Routes include nights, weekends, and holidays that fall within your workweek. Deliveries typically begin in the early morning, with pickups during the night.<br>• Trucks: Freightliners & Kenworth<br><br>🔴 Truck & Lease Info<br>• No money down | No credit check | Walkaway lease<br><br>• Current fleet mix is:<br>o 2022–2027 Freightliners<br>o 2022–2024 Kenworths<br>o 2026-2027 Kenworths<br>o 2025–2027 Volvos<br>o 2022-2023 trucks offer a mix of tractors with or without APUs. All 2024-2027 trucks do not have APUs.<br>• Lease terms: 2-5 years<br><br>• Up to 600,000 miles in maintenance coverage, subject to exclusions.<br>• ATBS Pre-Fund Call Required for contractors who choose the mileage contract<br>• Be prepared with current monthly expenses to build in a cash flow plan tailored to your business.<br>O Truck Pricing Summary: https://tinyurl.com/yyemactj<br><br>Costs<br>• Bobtail Coverage: $8.35/week per unit<br>• Bobtail Plus: $7.42/week per unit (deductible reduced to $250)<br>• Occupational Accident: $40.45/week per worker<br>• Physical Damage: $1.07 per $1,000 per week<br><br>🔴 Advantages<br>• Option for contractor to purchase lower-cost insurance coverage facilitated by U.S. Xpress.<br>• Become a trainer to increase compensation potential<br>• Pet policy: $500 pet fee, split into easy $50 weekly payments.<br><br>🔴Pay<br>• $1.00 per mile<br>$50 per stop<br><br><br>🔴Tagging<br>IC JOB: First Seat Driver<br>Solo/Team: Team<br>Area: Regional<br>Acct: Dedicated<br>Region: All<br>DED/Dom Term: Target Denton<br>ORIENTATION SITE:<br>Closest Site]]></description>
