      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED WALMART NEW CANEY -   3 mos exp required. Must live within 60 miles of New Caney TX. 2 drivers per week! Must have Personal Transportation to and from DC Daily</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Key Facts<br>*Night and weekend driving*<br>*Working Holidays*                                                    **11 PM Start Time**       <br><br>Key Selling Points:<br>*Home Daily*<br>*Tenured staff with family atmosphere*<br>*Paid Vacation*<br><br>If you live within 60 miles of New Caney, TX, you could be the perfect dedicated driver for our Walmart Grocery Dedicated team! Some of the best parts of being a dedicated driver are getting home DAILY and driving an average of 1600 miles per week. That’s an average of $1350 every week and up to $70k annually. In addition to mileage pay, you’ll earn $20 per stop.<br><br>Runs will include nights, weekends, and holidays that fall within your workweek. A typical workday will include 1-3 routes per day, with 1-3 stops each, and potentially a 10-hour break on the road each week.<br><br>FAQs:<br>* What will be my schedule?<br>You will be assigned two consecutive days off in the week based off our capacity needs. You will be expected to drive at nights, weekends, and on holidays. Your schedule will be assigned to you after you complete your ride along training and orientation.<br>* How much is my CPM?<br>Your CPM is based off verified driving experience (MOE). Check with your recruiter or DDES representative before you are released from orientation to verify your verified driving experience (MOE) to ensure that it’s correct and your CPM is correct.<br>* Do I get paid weekly?<br>Yes, you will be paid every Friday of each week. Pay period is from Monday -noon on Sunday.<br>* Do I have to unload the pallets at each store?<br>No, we are a no touch freight account, the store associates will physically offload the pallets. All you have to do is verify each pallet to ensure the proper pallets are going to the correct store and if the store has to remove another stores’ pallets then you are responsible to ensure that they product goes back on the trailer in the proper temp zones.<br>* Do I live unload or drop/hook at the stores?<br>All refrigerated deliveries are 100% live unload as the trailers have to be returned back to the DC to put back into rotation, if you encounter a situation where the store tells you to drop the trailer you have to contact your local office to get approval. There are selected stores on dry loads that are drop/hook, always check with your local team to make sure if you are not sure.<br><br><br>To give you the best possible driving experience…<br>• The DC includes 24/7 on-site staff, including safety support and a U.S. Xpress shop.<br>• After a year on the account, you can take a week of paid vacation.<br>o After 3 years – 2 weeks’ vacation<br>o After 7 years – 3 weeks vacation<br>• Paid onsite orientation and training runs.<br>o 1 Day Classroom Training - $50<br>o 2-3 Days ride-along training - $100/day<br><br>If this sounds like a good fit for you & your career, here are a few other operational details.<br>• Walmart is a 24/7 operation, with driving on nights, weekends, and holidays.<br>• Drive your personal vehicle to the DC each day and SLIPSEAT a newer model day cab or sleeper truck.<br>• Current schedule is 6 days worked/34-hour restart.<br>• Weekly off days are scheduled with your Transportation Manager once you arrive onsite.<br>• If a long mile load is not available, you will run 2-3 short loads to make your maximum pay for the day.<br>• Loads are a mixture of Dry and Refrigerated, no-touch grocery freight going to Walmart store locations in TX & LA.<br><br>Lane/Minimum Run Pay:<br>0-50 Miles: $40<br>51-75 Miles: $45<br>76-100 Miles: $55<br>101-125 Miles: $60<br>126-150 Miles: $65<br>151-175 Miles: $70<br>176-200 Miles: $75<br>201-225 Miles: $80<br>226+ Miles: CPM above<br><br>Experienced-Based CPM Pay:<br>0-6 Months: $.44<br>6 Months-1 Year: $.45<br>1 Year-2 Years: $.46<br>2 Years-3 Years: $.47<br>3 Years-5 Years: $.48<br>5 Years-7 Years: $.49<br>7 Years-10 Years: $.50<br>10+ Years: $.51<br><br>Stop Pay (all stops): $20<br><br>• Tagging<br>Job: Dedicated OTR Driver DLC<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: Local<br>Acct: Dedicated<br>Region: All<br>DED/Dom Term: Wal-Mart New Caney, TX<br>SIGN ON BONUS: Y/N]]></description>
