      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED OTR COMPANY DRIVERS ONLY. CALIFORNIA</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Key Selling Points:<br>Home Time:<br>We provide flexible scheduling to support work-life balance. Whether you prefer longer hauls to maximize earning potential or regionalized freight for more frequent home time, we’ll work with your preferences.<br><br>Nationwide OTR:<br>Our coverage spans all 48 states, with most freight running east of I-35- but we go where the freight takes us.<br><br>Mileage Average:<br>On average, drivers typically run around 2,000 miles per week, though this can vary depending on Hours of Service (HOS) and overall availability.<br><br>Our top performers—about 30% of our fleet—consistently run between 2,300-3,000+ miles per week.<br><br>To maximize your earnings, consider joining our trainer fleet:<br>• Earn an additional $250 per week while a student is on your truck<br>• Receive up to $1,000 in bonuses once your student upgrades<br>That’s an opportunity to earn up to $20,000 more per year.<br><br>Freight Type:<br>100% no-touch freight, with 50–60% drop & hook and 40–50% live unload.<br><br>No Forced NYC Dispatch:<br>You won’t be required to deliver into NYC or its five boroughs.<br><br>Equipment and Support:<br>• 2021 or newer Freightliner Cascadias or Kenworths.<br>• Average length of haul: 400 miles.<br>• 24/7 access to operations support, with empowered teams available around the clock.<br><br>Pay, Bonuses, and Benefits:<br>Detention Pay: $12.50 per hour after the second hour, unless a higher amount is required by state or local law.<br><br>Layover/Breakdown Pay: $100 per day, unless a higher amount is required by state or local law.<br><br>Performance Bonus: Earn up to an additional 3 CPM based on safety, mileage, and productivity, starting on the first of the month following your hire date. Must be an active OTR driver at the time of bonus payout to qualify.<br>Bonus eligibility requirements:<br>1. U.S. Xpress reserves the right to modify or cancel the Sign-On or Performance Bonus at any time with appropriate notice under applicable law.<br>2. Nothing in this Sign-On or Performance Bonus changes the at-will nature of your employment, meaning you and U.S. Xpress may terminate the employment relationship at any time, with or without cause.<br>3. You must be an active company driver on the day the bonus is paid.<br><br>Base Pay Range: per mile, based on experience and role.<br>https://tinyurl.com/3fe73c78<br>Vacation Package:<br>1 year = 1 week<br>3 years = 2 weeks<br>7 years = 3 weeks<br>15 years = 4 weeks<br><br>California Compliance:<br>We comply with California's paid sick leave laws and all applicable wage and hour laws for truck drivers.<br><br>Equal Opportunity Employer:<br>We are committed to providing equal employment opportunities regardless of age, gender, race, disability, or other protected categories.                                                                                  <br>*Tagging*<br>Orientation Site: Closest Terminal<br>Job: First Seat Driver<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: OTR<br>Acct: OTR<br>Region: WEST<br>Dedicated Domicile: Phoenix<br>South Florida: Y/N<br>Company: US Xpress 01<br>Updated 1.30.25]]></description>
