      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED USX Trainer Qualifications</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Trainer Requirements/Qualifications<br>	Drivers must have one year of OTR experience to be qualified to train.<br>	Drivers who upgraded at USX must have 9 months of OTR experience post upgrade to be eligible to train.<br>	Drivers must have 30 consecutive days with USX before being eligible to train.<br>	Drivers must have a good safety record and a good operational service record to be eligible to train:<br>•	In general, drivers cannot be on any type of probation.<br>•	Drivers cannot have had any preventable Class B accident in the last 6 months, and cannot have had any preventable Class C or Above accidents in the last 12 months. (The only exception is accidents classified by Safety as category A accidents.) <br>•	Drivers cannot have received any Unsafe CSA points in the last 6 months. <br>•	Driver cannot have been placed OOS (out of service) due to HOS (hours of service) or HazMat violations in the last 12 months.<br>•	Drivers should not have a record that indicates a poor attitude or difficulty dealing with Operations or customers.]]></description>
