      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[CLOSED O/OP paperwork and check list PLEASE REFER TO LEASE DEDICATED MAP TO SEE OPEN ACCOUNTS. LP'S DO NOT RECEIVE ORIENTATION PAY. OTR O/O MUST HAVE 9 months EXPERIENCE IN THE LAST 3 YRS. NO CA, NY, IL, NJ, CT, WA, OR, MA, MD, PA. ]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[• PLEASE REFER TO LEASE DEDICATED MAP TO SEE OPEN ACCOUNTS <br><br><br>• Must have 9 months verifiable tractor trailer experience in the last 3 years<br>• Must attend orientation at any terminal<br>• Truck must be 10 years old or newer <br>• Must pass DOT inspection at USX terminal at time of leasing<br>• 270 inch wheelbase or less, 13 ft tall stacks or taller, 48 inch fifth-wheel height or lower<br><br>• Non-Forced Dispatch. O/O determine their home time but are advised to stay out at least 10-12 days before taking home time. O/O are responsible for managing their expenses at all times.<br><br>• USX does not use a load board for O/O. By dispatching drivers using load optimization technology, we’re able to keep drivers planned out and moving rather than shopping for the best load.<br><br>• Pay:<br>0-200 miles $2.00 per mile<br><br>201-400 miles $1.15 per mile<br><br>401+ miles $1.02 per mile<br><br>70% of stop pay up to $55 per stop<br> <br><br>Mileage rate and fuel surcharge paid on all dispatched miles. Fuel surcharge changes weekly dependent on national fuel average.<br><br>Most dedicated accounts hiring USX Company Lease Purchase drivers will also take owner ops, must ask account manager for current needs.<br><br><br>- O/O Team $1.02 per mile ($100 minimum) ($50.00 minimum)<br><br> <br><br>• All documents must be sent to Contractor Administrator and approved before scheduling orientation.<br><br>• Truck Purchased<br>- Copy of previous IRP registration (cab card). If you don’t have it, it must be retitled in Oklahoma.<br>or TN Owner’s Authorization Form<br>- Bill of Sale<br>- Title, front and back (Seller)<br>- Title Receipt (Purchaser)<br>- 2290<br><br>• Truck Leased Through a Third Party<br>- Copy of previous IRP registration (cab card). If you don’t have it, it must be retitled in Oklahoma.<br>or TN Owner’s Authorization Form, signed by Truck Lessor<br>- Truck Lease<br>- Title, front and back<br>- 2290<br><br>- You must have an EIN to pay 2290. To get an EIN assigned, visit: IRS EIN Individual Request<br><br>- We must have your 2290 Schedule 1 receipt to run USX base plates. To receive this at our discounted rate, please visit: E-file Form 2290 with US Xpress ( www.usxpress2290.com )<br><br>- The $550.00 annual amount for 2290 is due July 1st, each year. (Prorated each month if purchased after).<br><br>- To pay a business, we need a copy of the Articles of Organization, a W-9, a letter from the IRS showing EIN assignment (Form SS4), and a voided check for the business account for direct deposit.<br><br>- USX covers base plates, permits, EZ pass, pre-pass, cargo liability insurance, and our full fuel discount.<br><br>- If a driver has their own DOT authority and would like to run freight for USX, transfer to:<br>Brokerage Department ext. ext. 6583 • Tagging<br>IC Job: First Seat Driver (FSD)<br>Solo/Team: solo<br>Area: Account Chosen<br>Acct: Account Chosen<br>Region: Account Chosen<br>DED/Dom Term: THL<br>SIGN ON BONUS: N]]></description>
