      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED WALMART HAMMOND (ROBERT LA) **NO HARVEY LA DRIVERS** - Home Daily/local. Drivers need to live within the shaded area. Drivers work a 6 day work week, off for 34 hour reset weekly. Drivers will slip seat in a daycab and will need a personal vehicle to and from the DC. 1 day of in-classroom training in which you’ll receive $50 and 2-3 days of ride-along training at $100 per day. Account is a 24/7 operations and starting night shift only, running weekends and holidays</name>
        <description><![CDATA[DC Address 45346 Parkway Blvd.| Robert, LA. 70455-2221<br><br>Restrictions<br>•	No New Orleans or Baton Rouge, LA drivers<br>•	Location Requirement: Drivers must live within the hiring area (shaded area).<br>•	Slip Seat Operation: Drivers will need to use a personal vehicle to reliably commute to and from the Robert, LA Distribution Center (DC).<br>Job Details<br>•	Freight: Mix of dry and refrigerated no-touch grocery freight delivering to Walmart and Sam's Club locations in LA, TX, MS, AL and FL.<br>•	Shifts: Expected start time will be between 5pm-7pm, with weekends required. With other shifts becoming available upon increased tenure at account.<br>•	Mileage: Average of 1500-1600 miles per week.<br>•	Paid Stops: Paid for each stop + the miles. <br>•	Work Schedule: Home Daily. Choose to Work 5 with 2 days off -OR- choose to work 6 with 1 day off. <br>•	Training:<br>o	1 day of paid classroom training ($50)<br>o	4 days of paid ride-along training <br>Key Requirements<br>•	Home Daily: Must have personal transportation to reliably commute to the DC in Robert, LA.<br>•	Shift Flexibility: Must be Available to work nights, weekends, and holidays that fall on normal work schedule.<br>•	Experience: Must be within the hiring area and meet experience requirements for pay scale.<br>•	Truck Type: Newer model day cabs. This is a slip seat operation meaning you would share different trucks with other drivers on the account. <br>Benefits<br>•	Home Daily: Drivers return home daily after completing their shifts.<br>•	Industry-Leading Pay Package: Average $1,100 weekly. Top earners can earn $1,500+<br>•	Stop Pay: $20 per stop.<br>•	Support: Tenured 24/7 operations staff and shop support for drivers. <br>•	No-Touch Freight: Walmart grocery freight does not require driver unloads.<br>•	Vacation:<br>o	1 week of paid vacation after 1 year of service<br>o	2 weeks after 2 years<br>o	3 weeks after 7 years, <br>o	Accumulating up to 4 weeks at 10 years.<br>Pay Structure<br>•	Lane/Minimum Run Pay:<br>o	0-50 Miles: $40<br>o	51-75 Miles: $45<br>o	76-100 Miles: $60<br>o	101-125 Miles: $70<br>o	126-150 Miles: $75<br>o	151-175 Miles: $80<br>o	176-200 Miles: $85<br>o	201-225 Miles: $90<br>o	226+ Miles: Paid per mile based on experience.<br>•	Stop Pay: $20 per stop.<br>Experience-Based Pay<br>•	0-6 months: $0.40/mile<br>•	6 months-1 year: $0.44/mile<br>•	1-2 years: $0.45/mile<br>•	2-3 years: $0.46/mile<br>•	3-5 years: $0.47/mile<br>•	5-7 years: $0.48/mile<br>•	7-10 years: $0.49/mile<br>•	10+ years: $0.50/mile<br>Note: If a long load is not available, drivers will run 2-3 shorter loads to maximize daily pay. Each order will pay whichever is greater (mileage pay or flat rate pay). <br><br>Tagging<br>Job: Dedicated OTR Driver - DLC<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: Local<br>Acct: Dedicated<br>Region: All<br>DED Dom Term: Walmart Hammond<br>SIGN ON BONUS: Y/N                                                Updated 11.5.24]]></description>
