      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED FXG Team 3 months exp required 200 miles of Bloomington, CA. - $1700 weekly True Up. Teams will be out 2-3 weeks at a time. $12 K SOB Split or $15K SOB SPLIT!  NEED DOUBLES ENDORSEMENT PRIOR TO COMING IN! NEED 5 TEAMS
</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Key Facts:<br>•	Teams will be out 2-3 weeks at a time <br>•	Must have doubles endorsements upon arrival to account.<br>•	Driver coupled pups.<br>•	Patience with customer/customer service skills required.<br>•	Must live within a 100-mile radius of their team partner.<br><br><br>Key Selling Points:<br>•	$12,000 or $15,000 sign-on bonus split.<br>•	$1,700 weekly true-up.<br>•	Drivers who run 5,000 miles make an average of $2,000 weekly.<br>•	Tenured staff to support you.<br><br>FAQ:<br>•	Are 28' pups more dangerous than 53' trailers?<br>•	Negative, on the contrary, we have one of the best accidents per million mile in the company. We provide a 3-day class (paid at $150 per day) to ensure you are comfortable with coupling/uncoupling and moving the dolly.<br>•	What states do I deliver to?<br>•	All 48 states. However, we rarely go to NY. This is a customer planned account. FXG sends over preplanned week-long lanes for each truck. USXD Ops does not adjust the lanes.<br>•	How much money will I make?<br>•	Drivers who run 5,000 miles make an average of $2,000 weekly. Top earners (0.90cpm) can earn north of $115,000 annually.<br>•	What shift will I work?<br>•	As a team, the truck is in continuous motion. You coordinate with your partner what shift you prefer.<br>•	When can I take a vacation?<br>•	After 1 year, you will get 1 week's vacation. After 2 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 7 years, 3 weeks. This totals up to 4 weeks at 10 years.<br>•	What kind of truck will I get?<br>•	Our fleet is comprised of Freightliners. Each truck must be equipped with a Pintle hook to couple and uncouple the pups. This is done during doubles training class and provided by the shop.<br>•	What is a true-up? How do I qualify for the true-up?<br>•	Work as directed, be on-time, and be available 6 days out of the week for weekly lane dispatch. True up is in place to protect your salary should there be any delays at the shipper, breakdowns, or weather delays. This trumps layover pay as well. Our minimum weekly pay is $1,700 as long as the above conditions are met.<br><br>Additional Account Details:<br>•	We will provide 3 days of Doubles training at $150 per day.<br>• Training will be in Ellenwood<br>•	All teams need to be paired prior<br><br><br>Pay Scale Based on EACH driver's Verified experience<br>LESS THAN 12 MONTHS: 72 CPM SPLIT<br>1 YEAR- .73 CPM SPLIT<br>2 YEARS- .74 CPM SPLIT<br>3 YEARS- .76 CPM SPLIT<br>4 YEARS- .78 CPM SPLIT<br>5 YEARS- .80 CPM SPLIT<br>6 YEARS- .82 CPM SPLIT<br>7 YEARS- .84 CPM SPLIT<br>8 YEARS- .86 CPM SPLIT<br>9 YEARS- .88 CPM SPLIT<br>10 YEARS- .90 CPM SPLIT<br><br>Sign on Bonus: team drivers will qualify for one of the below payouts<br>• $12K bonus: if a driver needs to be matched with a teammate, or if a pre-made team comes in under a year of driving experience together, they will receive a $12K split sign on bonus ($6K per driver)<br>$12K payout:<br>each driver is paid $500 paid after 1st load, $500 paid at 30 days, $1,000 paid out monthly for 5 months<br><br>• $15K bonus: if a team comes in with 1 full year of verifiable driving experience together, they will receive a $15K split sign on bonus ($7.5K per driver)<br>15k sign-on bonus split, each team partner bonus installments are listed below:<br>• $250 paid after 1st load<br>• $250 paid at 30 days<br>• $1,000 paid at 60 days $1500 each @ 2 Months!<br>• $750 paid at 150 days<br>• $750 paid at 240 days<br>• $750 paid at 330 days<br>• $750 paid at 365 days $4.5k each @ 1 year!<br>• $750 paid at 455 days<br>• $750 paid at 545 days<br>• $750 paid at 635 days<br>• $750 paid at 725 days $7.5k each @ 2 years!<br><br>Tagging<br>Job: Dedicated OTR Driver<br>Solo/Team: TEAM<br>Area: OTR<br>Acct: Dedicated<br>Region: All<br>Ded Tour: FXG<br>DED/Dom Term: FXG<br>Team Partner<br>Team Bonus<br>Pre-made                                                                       Orientation Site: Closest Terminal]]></description>
