      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED Target Lugoff SC - 3 months. NEED 3 DRIVERS! experience required  - home weekly drivers need to live within 60 miles of Lugoff SC - New hire drivers pay and training time -$100 per day 1-2 day ride along.                       </name>
        <description><![CDATA[Key Facts<br>*Patience with Customer/Customer Service Skills Required*<br>*Night and early morning Driving<br>**Weekend and Holiday driving required*<br><br>Key Selling Points<br>*Can be home most days<br>*Drop and Hook freight<br>*Drivers who run 2200 miles make an average of $1100 weekly*<br>*Tenured staff to support you*<br><br>FAQ<br>* How hard is the driver unload?<br>No driver touch – all freight unloaded by customer. <br>* What States do I deliver to<br>VA, NC, SC, GA <br>* How much money will I make?<br>Drivers who run the average pf 2200 miles make an average of $1100 weekly<br>* When is my home time and 34 hour reset?<br>If you are in the area of your home – you can take the truck home as long as there is a safe place to park the truck. Dispatch will make sure you are home for reset if you choose. <br>* What shift will I work?<br>Target ships freight days, nights, weekends, and holidays. <br>* When can I take a Vacation?<br>After 1 year you will get 1 weeks vacation and after 2 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 7 years, 3 weeks. This totals up to 4 weeks at 10 years!<br>* What kind of truck will I get?<br>Our fleet is comprised of Internationals, Freightliners and Kenworths<br><br>If you live within 60 miles of Lugoff, SC, you could be the perfect dedicated driver to add to our Target team! Some of the best parts of being a dedicated driver are getting home WEEKLY, and driving an average of 2,100-2,500 per week. That’s around $1100-$1200 every week and up to $58,000 annually. <br> <br>As part of the target dedicated team, you’ll run DRY, NO-TOUCH freight to various TARGET locations in SC, GA, VA, NC – all within 600 miles of the LUGOFF distribution center. ALL FREIGHT IS ON PRELOADED TRAILERS AND WILL BE A DROP/HOOK UNLOAD.<br><br>To give you the best possible driving experience, the distribution center includes 24/7 on-site staff, including safety support and a U.S. Xpress shop WITHIN 100 MILES. <br><br>Runs will include nights, weekends, and holidays that fall within your workweek. Routes also typically require 1-2 stops per DAY and potentially a [10]-hour break on the road each week. <br><br>But being a dedicated driver is no easy task. So, the way we see it, you deserve vacation time more than anyone. That’s why after 1 year you will get 1 week vacation and after 2 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 7 years, 3 weeks. This totals up to 4 weeks at 10 years!<br><br>If you choose to join the team, you’ll go through a short orientation to help get you started on the right foot. And you’ll get paid to do it. You’ll attend one day of in-classroom training in which you’ll receive $100, and 1-2 days of ride-along training at $100 per day.<br><br>• Payscale Based On Verified Experience<br>0-5 $0.44<br>6-11 $0.45<br>12-23 $0.46<br>24-35 $0.47<br>36-47 $0.48<br>48-59 $0.49<br>5+ years $0.50<br><br><br>• Tagging<br>Job: Dedicated OTR Driver DLC<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: Regional<br>Account: Dedicated<br>Dedicated or Domicile Terminal: Target Lugoff<br>Sign on Bonus: Y/N]]></description>
