      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED Ollie’s Commerce GA Must live within 50 miles of Commerce, GA. Home Weekly. $1350 weekly average pay!
</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Key Facts<br>• Regional Freight, Home Weekly for 34-hour Resets<br>• No Touch Freight<br>• Consistent Routes<br>• Average Weekly Pay $1,350 <br>• Top earners can earn up to $78,000 per year<br><br>Key Selling Points<br>• Drivers average 5 routes per week<br>• Drivers average 1680-miles per week within the following region: AL, GA, TN, SC, NC, VA<br>• Store Deliveries between 0400 and Noon. Trailers consist of 1-2 stops <br>• Service Orientated Account – Drivers are expected to follow dispatch times for pick up and deliveries. Drivers are required to take his/her 10-hour break behind stop #1 prior to offload<br>• Drivers work week averages 5.5 days per week, 34-hour resets weekly<br>• No Touch Freight and Drivers must live within 50-mi of DC.<br><br><br>As part of the Ollie’s Dedicated team, you’ll run No-Touch freight to various Ollie’s store locations in the southeast. Freight is live-unload with some drop and hook. Freight is no touch, but drivers are required to strap the load at the origin and in between stops<br>To give you the best possible driving experience, our dedicated staff provides 24/7 availability, including safety support and a U.S. Xpress shop.<br>Runs will include nights, weekends, and holidays that fall within your workweek. Routes also typically require 1-2 stops per load and 10-hour break behind the 1st delivery store prior to offload.<br><br>Pay Scale-By Lane <br>Drivers average $0.77 per mile <br>Lanes less than 100 Miles pay $82.39 per load<br><br><br>Stop Pay $25.00/stop after the first stop<br>Vacation Pay – Company Standards<br>• 1 year = 1 week<br>• 3 years = 2 weeks<br>• 7 years = 3 weeks<br>• 15 years = 4 weeks<br><br>• TAGGING<br>Job: Dedicated OTR Driver - DLC<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: Regional<br>Acct: Dedicated<br>Region: All<br>DED/Dom Term: Ollie’s Commerce]]></description>
