      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[CLOSED Dollar Tree Ocala FL- 1 driver per week!! Minimum weekly $1100 Weekly True Up!!!  Drivers need to have 2 weeks' worth of supplies when they arrive to orientation. Once they activate they will be sent directly to Ocala, FL to report for training. Drivers WILL seat a truck with a current DT Driver.  New hires assigned to tractors AFTER completing 1 week ride along time with current driver at $150 per day. Drivers must have secure parking location for truck and trailer.]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[*Drivers need to have 2 weeks' worth of supplies when they arrive to orientation. Once they activate, they will be sent directly to Ocala FL to report for training.*                                                                                                                                  Account key selling points<br>*Driver Manual Unload*<br>*Patience with Customer/Customer Service Skills Required*<br>*Not home daily or every weekend*<br><br>Key Selling Points<br><br>*Pay Package for the area is industry-leading*<br>*Drivers who run 800 miles and 4 loads make an average of $1,150-$1,580 weekly*<br>*Tenured staff to support you*<br>*Minimum Home Weekly*<br>https://vimeo.com/507100528/da4b42c25c         <br>https://vimeo.com/669499314<br><br>FAQ<br>* How hard is the driver unload?<br>It is a challenging hard job but is very financially rewarding and great exercise, it can take some time to acclimate to the unload. We will support you thought the whole process!<br>* What States do I deliver to<br>Florida<br>* How much money will I make?<br>Drivers who run 800 miles and 4 loads make an average of $1,150-$1,580 weekly depending on experience<br>* When is my home time and 34 hour reset?<br>we do get you home weekly.<br>* What shift will I work?<br>With most DT deliveries starting in the early AM you will either be driving to your first stop the night before and taking a reset or driving in the early morning to make on time delivery. From there you will deliver throughout the day to multiple DT stores. <br>* When can I take a Vacation?<br>After 1 year you will get 1 weeks vacation and after 2 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 7 years, 3 weeks. This totals up to 4 weeks at 10 years!<br>* What kind of truck will I get?<br>Our fleet is comprised of Internationals, Freightliners and Kenworths<br>* What is a True-Up? How do I qualify for the True-Up? <br>Work as directed, be on-time, and be available for Dispatch M-S as long as hours of service permits.<br><br>If you live within 100 miles of Ocala, Florida, you could be the perfect dedicated driver to add to our Dollar Tree team! Some of the best parts of being a dedicated driver are getting home at a minimum of every other day, and driving an average of 800 miles per week. That’s around $1,150-$1,580 every week and up to $60,000-$82,000 annually depending on experience. On this account, all drivers are paid a per mile rate of between $.48 and $1.01 and $200 per trailer unload depending on experience<br> <br>As part of the Dollar Tree dedicated team, you’ll run dry full touch freight to various Dollar Tree locations in Florida – all within 150 miles of the Ocala, Florida distribution center. 100% of freight will be live unloaded at Dollar Tree stores.<br><br>Runs will include nights, weekends, and holidays that fall within your workweek. Routes also typically require 3-5 stops per day and potentially a 10-hour break on the road each day. <br><br>But being a dedicated driver is no easy task. So, the way we see it, you deserve vacation time more than anyone. That’s why after a year on the account, you can take a week of paid vacation. After 2 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 10 years, 3 weeks.<br><br>If you choose to join the team, you’ll go through a short orientation to help get you started on the right foot. And you’ll get paid to do it. You’ll attend one day of in-classroom training in which you’ll receive $150, and 3 days of ride-along training at $150 per day.<br><br>.<br>• Payscale Based On Verified Experience<br>Experience (Years) CPM<br>0 months $ 0.480<br>6 months $ 0.500<br>1 year $ 0.530<br>2 year $ 0.560<br>3 year $ 0.590<br>4 year $ 0.620<br>5 year $ 0.650<br>6 year $ 0.680<br>7 year $ 0.710<br>8 year $ 0.750<br>9 year $ 0.790<br>10 year $ 0.830<br>11 year $ 0.870<br>12 year $ 0.910<br>13 year $ 0.960<br>14 year $ 1.010<br><br>Unload $200 per trailer<br>$1100 weekly true up pay as long as driver is available 5.5 days<br><br><br>• Tagging<br>Job: Dedicated OTR Driver - DLC<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: Regional<br>Acct: Dedicated<br>Region:]]></description>
