      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[CLOSED Michael's Berlin, NJ. Must live within 50 miles of Berlin, NJ. Home Weekly. $1100 weekly true up! Need 3 drivers. Please email Driver Placement if you book a driver for this account. ]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[Key Facts<br>•	Regional Freight, Home Weekly for 34-hour Resets<br>•	No Touch Freight<br>•	Consistent Routes<br>•	Average Weekly Pay $1,415 based on experience<br>•	Top earners can earn up to $73,500 per year<br><br>Key Selling Points<br>•	Drivers average 2 – 3 routes per week<br>•	Drivers average 1730-miles per week within the following region: CT, PA, NJ, NC, SC (1-location Rock Hill), VA, WV (1-location Martinsburg) <br>•	Store Deliveries between midnight and 0600. Trailers consist of 1-4 stops, pending time of year<br>•	Service Orientated Account – Drivers are expected to follow dispatch times for pick up and deliveries. Drivers are required to take his/her 10-hour break behind stop #1 prior to offload<br>•	Drivers are expected to be available 5.5 days per week, 34-hour rests are done on Saturdays pending customer’s demand but not guaranteed<br>•	No Touch Freight and Drivers must live within 50-mi of DC.<br>•	True Up Pay $1100/week if all account objectives are met<br><br><br>If you live within 50 miles of the Berlin, NJ, you could be the perfect dedicated driver to add to our Dedicated Michaels team! Some of the best parts of being a dedicated driver are getting home weekly and driving an average of 1736 miles per week. That’s around $1,415 every week and up to $73,500 annually. Top earners can make $80,000 annually. <br>As part of the Michaels dedicated team, you’ll run Dry No-Touch freight to various Michaels store locations as far north as Connecticut and as far south as North Carolina – all within 600-miles of the Berlin distribution center. 100% of freight will be live unloaded at Michaels stores.<br>To give you the best possible driving experience, our dedicated staff provides 24/7 availability, including safety support and a U.S. Xpress shop.<br>Each driver plays a key role in providing exceptional on time service to our dedicated customer (Expectation is 100% on time Service). Runs will include nights, weekends, and holidays that fall within your workweek. Routes also typically require 1-4 stops per load and 10-hour break behind the 1st delivery store prior to offload.<br>But being a dedicated driver is no easy task. So, the way we see it, you deserve vacation time more than anyone. That’s why after a year on the account, you can take a week of paid vacation. After 3 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 7 years, 3 weeks.<br><br>Pay Scale – Based on Verifiable Experience –<br>•	0 Months - $0.54/mi<br>•	6 Months - $0.55/mi<br>•	12 Months - $0.56/mi<br>•	24 Months - $0.57/mi<br>•	36 Months - $0.58/mi<br>•	48 Months - $0.59/mi<br>•	60 Months - $0.60/mi<br>•	72 Months - $0.62/mi<br>•	84 Months - $0.64/mi<br>•	96 Months - $0.66/mi<br>•	108 Months - $0.68/mi<br>•	120 Months - $0.70/mi<br><br>Stop Pay $35.00/stop<br>Weekly True Up Pay: $1100<br>Vacation Pay – Company Standards<br>•	1 year = 1 week<br>•	3 years = 2 weeks<br>•	7 years = 3 weeks<br>•	15 years = 4 weeks<br><br>• TAGGING<br>Job: Dedicated OTR Driver - DLC<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: Regional<br>Acct: Dedicated<br>Region: All<br>DED/Dom Term: Michael’s Berlin]]></description>
