      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED DT COWPENS, SC-3 mos exp. 34 hour reset weekly  Minimum $1200 weekly true up pay and extra $250 incentive for 3 DT Store Unloads!! Once they activate they will be sent directly to Cowpens, SC to report for training.
New hires assigned to tractors AFTER completing 1 week ride along time with current driver at $150 per day. 4 Per Week. Drivers must have secure parking location for truck and trailer.</name>
        <description><![CDATA[**Cannot hire drivers running account currently or if they have departed from these carriers within the last 6 months without going to another carrier first—<br>• Hogan<br>• CR England<br><br>Job Description:<br>We are currently seeking a dedicated driver to join our team at Dollar Tree Cowpens.. As a dedicated driver, you will run 100% TOUCH freight to various Dollar Tree locations in SC, VA, WVA, NC, GA, AL, TN. The job requires running an average of 1300 miles per week and making up to 3 stops per day. The role also requires the driver to be away from home for extended periods, including nights, weekends, and holidays that fall within the workweek. *Drivers need to have 2 weeks' worth of supplies when they arrive to orientation. Once they activate, they will be sent directly to Cowpens, SC to report for training. Drivers WILL seat a truck with a current DT Driver. *<br><br>Key Selling Points:<br>• Competitive industry-leading pay package <br>• Drivers can earn an average of $1450 up to $1600 weekly<br> • Unload pay of $235 per load inclusive at all stops <br>• Minimum home weekly<br>• Tenured staff for support <br>• Eligible for a $250 incentive if drivers deliver 3 Dollar Tree store delivery loads each week<br> • Paid vacation after 1 year on the account<br><br><br>FAQ:<br>1.	What is the average weekly earnings potential for the job? Answer: Drivers can earn an average of $1600 weekly.<br>2.	What is the work schedule like? Answer: Runs include nights, weekends, and holidays that fall within your workweek. Routes also typically require 4 stops per day and potentially a 34-hour break on the road each week.<br><br>Pay:<br>• Pay scale based on verified experience <br>0 .44<br>12 .47<br>24 .49<br>36 .50<br>48 .51<br>60 .52<br>84 .53<br>120+ .54<br>• Unload pay of $235 per load inclusive at all stops<br>• Backhaul pay of $45<br>• Minimum weekly true up pay of $1200<br>• Extra $40 weekly incentive if the driver is available for a full work week<br><br> •Tagging<br>Job: Dedicated OTR Driver - DLC<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: Regional<br>Acct: Dedicated<br>Region: All<br>DED/Dom Term: DT Cowpens                                               PST: Required                  <br>SIGN ON BONUS: Y/N  ]]></description>
