      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED Michaels New Lenox IL - need to live 100 miles of New Lenox IL (ZIP 60451)- 3 months exp required True Up of $1300 per week! Need 3 drivers</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Michaels New Lenox IL - need to live 100 miles of New Lenox IL (ZIP 60451)- 3 months exp required True Up of $1300 per week! <br>Key Facts<br>* Regional, Home Weekly for 34 Resets<br>* No Touch Freight<br>* $1300 Weekly True Up if all requirements are met<br>* Consistent Routes<br><br>Key Selling Points<br>* No touch Freight. Deliveries start between Midnight and 0600.<br>* Drivers will service Michaels Store deliveries out of their DC located in New Lenox, IL to the following states: IL, IA, IN, KY, MI, MN, MO, NE, SD, WI, TN.<br>* Drivers average 1750 miles per week.<br>* Drivers average 3-5 loads per week.<br><br>If you live within 100 miles of New Lenox, IL, you could be the perfect dedicated driver to add to our Dedicated Michaels team! Some of the best parts of being a dedicated driver are getting home weekly, and driving an average of 1750 miles per week. That’s around $1400 every week and up to $80,000 annually.<br><br>As part of the Michaels dedicated team, you’ll run Dry No-Touch freight to various Michaels Store locations in IL, IA, IN, KY, MI, MN, MO, NE, SD, WI, TN – all within 600-miles of the New Lenox distribution center. 100% of freight will be live unloaded at Michaels stores.<br><br>To give you the best possible driving experience, our dedicated staff provides 24/7 availability, including safety support and a U.S. Xpress shop.<br><br>Each driver plays a key role in providing exceptional on time service to our dedicated customer (Expectation is 100% on time Service). Runs will include nights, weekends, and holidays that fall within your workweek. Routes also typically require 2-4 stops per load and 10-hour break behind the 1st delivery store prior to offload.<br><br>But being a dedicated driver is no easy task. So, the way we see it, you deserve vacation time more than anyone. That’s why after a year on the account, you can take a week of paid vacation. After 3 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 7 years, 3 weeks.<br><br>• Payscale Based On Verified Experience<br>0 Months $0.52/mi<br>6 Months $0.53/mi<br>12 Months $0.54/mi<br>24 Months $0.55/mi<br>36 Months $0.56/mi<br>48 Months $0.57/mi<br>60 Months $0.58/mi<br>72 Months $0.59/mi<br>84 Months $0.60/mi<br>96 Months $0.61/mi<br>108 Months $0.62/mi<br>120 Months $0.63/mi<br><br>Stop Pay $35.00/stop (Valid for every stop after the 1st Stop)<br>Load Pay $20.00/Load<br>Weekly True Up Pay: $1300                                                  <br>Tagging<br>Job: DLC<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: Regional<br>Acct: Dedicated<br>Region: All<br>DED/Dom Term: Michael's New Lenox IL<br>Sign on Bonus: Y/N<br>Orientation Site: Closest Terminal ]]></description>
