      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED LIDL Perryville, MD (Pronounced Leedle)- Drivers must live within 30 miles of Perryville, MD
Home daily and run at your pace!
$1825-$2200 per week!!
Can Earn $91-$115k based on experience. Need 5 drivers. PLEASE EMAIL DRIVER PLACEMENT WHEN YOU BOOK A DRIVER FOR THIS ACCOUNT 
</name>
        <description><![CDATA[**Cannot hire drivers current drivers with:<br>SCHNEIDER<br>CR England<br>NFI<br><br>Key Facts<br>*Loading and unload trailers *<br>*Night driving required*<br>*Avg LOH is 380 with 3 stops*<br>*Delivers to NYC and surrounding area *<br>SLIP SEAT<br>NO SOB<br>*Load/Unload using Powered Pallet Jacks*<br><br>Key Selling Points<br>* Home Daily *<br>* Pay Package for the area is industry-leading*<br>* Drivers who are avail for 5 shifts average $2,055-$2265 depending on verified experience<br>* Opportunity for 6th day bonus’ and weekend bonus’ $100 for each on top of day rate.<br>* $100 bonus for any loads delivering into NYC borough’s<br>*Tenured staff to support you*<br><br>FAQ<br>* How hard is the driver load/ unload?<br>It is a challenging hard job but is very financially rewarding and great exercise, it can take some time to acclimate to the unload. We will support you thought the whole process!<br>* What States do I deliver to<br>PA, NJ, NYC/ Long Island, NY, CT<br>* How much money will I make?<br>Depending on experience $2,055-$2265<br>When is my home time and 34 hour reset?<br>* Drivers will be home after their shift.<br>What shift will I work?<br> Nights<br>* When can I take a Vacation?<br>After 1 year you will get 1 weeks vacation and after 2 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 7 years, 3 weeks. This totals up to 4 weeks at 10 years!<br>* What kind of truck will I get?<br>Our fleet is comprised of Internationals, Freightliners and Kenworths. All Day cabs<br><br>If you live within 30 miles of Perryville, MD, you could be the perfect dedicated driver to add to our LIDL team! Some of the best parts of being a dedicated driver are getting home DAILY and driving an average of 1100-1500 miles per week. That’s around $2055-$2265 every week and up to $91k-$115k annually. In addition to mileage pay, you’ll earn $100 bonus for working Saturday, $100 for working Sunday. Borough Pay is $100 per load and average 2-3 per week<br><br>As part of the LIDL dedicated team, you’ll run DRY/REFRIGERATED, TOUCH freight to various LIDL locations in NYC and surrounding areas.<br>To give you the best possible driving experience, the distribution center includes 24/7 on-site staff, including safety support and a U.S. Xpress shop.<br><br>Runs will include nights, weekends, and holidays that fall within your workweek. Routes also typically require 3 stops per load and 1-2 loads per night.<br><br>But being a dedicated driver is no easy task. So, the way we see it, you deserve vacation time more than anyone. That’s why after a year on the account, you can take a week of paid vacation.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         1 year - 1 week<br>2 years - 2 weeks<br>5 years - 3 weeks<br>7 years - 4 weeks <br>Paid as a 52 week average<br><br>Weekly Salary Pay Scale<br>Total Experience Weekly Salary<br>0 Month $1,825.00<br>6 Months $1,845.00<br>12 Months $1,860.00<br>24 Months $1,880.00<br>36 Months $1,900.00<br>48 Months $1,920.00<br>60 Months $1,935.00<br>72 Months $1,955.00<br>84 Months $1,975.00<br>96 Months $1,995.00<br>108 Months $2,015.00<br>120 Months $2,035.00<br><br><br>• Borough Pay: $100 per load and average 2.3 per week<br>Potential of $230 more per week<br>•LOH 280 with 3 stops.<br><br>• Any driver working a weekend shift will receive a bonus: $100 for Saturday and $100 Sunday.<br><br><br>• Tagging<br>Job: Dedicated OTR Driver DLC<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: LOCAL<br>Account: Dedicated<br>Dedicated or Domicile Terminal: LIDL Perryville<br>PST: Required <br>SIGN ON BONUS: Y/N  ]]></description>
