      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED Home Depot Baytown--Local Home Daily. Must live within 60 miles of Baytown, TX and have personal transportation to and from the DC daily. NEED 2 DRIVERS. EMAIL DRIVER PLACEMENT WHEN YOU BOOK A DRIVER FOR THIS FLEET.</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Key Selling Points:<br>Home Daily<br>Consistent Pay<br>Desirable Schedule (Weekday Daytime)<br><br>Risks: <br>Working Holidays (If fall during the week)<br><br><br>FAQs:<br>Q. It’s a salary, whats the catch? <br><br>A. If you are available for work everyday, you will be paid the weekly salary. The work load and tasks each day may vary, but the pay is consistent. If you are unavailable for a day, then one day of pay is deducted from your check. <br><br>Q. It was a slow day and I only ran one load, how much will I get paid?<br>A.	The same everyday. There will be busy days and slow days, but the pay is consistent. If you are available, you will be paid for the day. This provides stability to in your check every week. <br>Q. It was a busy day, do I get paid extra?<br>A.	The same everyday. Just as you are still paid the same for the slow days. There will be busy days for the customer and everyone will need to step up and meet the need. While there will be busy and slow days, you will always get a consistent, predictable check.<br><br>Q. Is there any way to earn extra pay?<br><br>A.	The weekly salary is based on a 5 day work week. If want to work an extra day, we will find work. If you work a 6th day (or possibly even a 7th), you will earn an additional day of pay (or possibly 2). <br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>If you live within 60 miles of Baytown, TX, you could be the perfect dedicated driver to add to our Home Depot Dedicated team! Some of the best parts of being a dedicated driver are getting home DAILY and driving an average of 1000 miles per week. That’s a salary of $1153.84 every week and $60k annually. <br> <br>As part of the Home Depot Dedicated team, you’ll run DRY NO-TOUCH freight to various Home Depot locations in TX – all within 250 miles of the Home Depot Baytown distribution center. 90% of freight will be live unloaded at Home Depot stores.<br><br>To give you the best possible driving experience, the distribution center includes daytime on-site staff to support you. <br><br>Runs will include daytime weekdays (M-F) and holidays that fall within your workweek. A typical workday will include 1-3 routes with 1-2 stops each and 10 hour break at home. <br><br>But being a dedicated driver is no easy task. So, the way we see it, you deserve vacation time more than anyone. That’s why after a year on the account, you can take a week of paid vacation. After 3 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 7 years, 3 weeks.<br><br>If you choose to join the team, you’ll go through a short orientation on site to help get you started on the right foot. And you’ll get paid to do it.<br><br>If this sounds like a good fit for you & your career, here are a few other operational details:<br>•	You will drive your personal vehicle to the DC each day to report to work<br>•	Besides DC-Store deliveries (no touch), there could be work doing other activities including but not limited to: pallet and DC transfers, equipment repositioning(to a shop for service as an example) and supporting other nearby accounts for the day (again no touch). <br><br><br><br>Pay<br>$1153.84 Salary per week<br><br>• Tagging<br>Job: Local Driver<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: LOCAL<br>Account: Dedicated<br>Dedicated or Domicile Terminal: Home Depot Baytown TX]]></description>
