      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED Fed EX Ground Solo  - 60 miles of Ellenwood GA -$12k SOB!!! Requires Doubles Endorsement prior to orientation - Drivers can  obtain endorsement at DMV( 10-12 question test) NEED 5 DRIVERS ONLY. PLEASE EMAIL DRIVER PLACEMENT WHEN YOU HAVE BOOKED A DRIVER FOR THIS ACCOUNT
</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Key Facts			<br>					*Must be able to get doubles Endorsements upon arrival to account*			<br>					*Driver coupled pups*			<br>					*Patience with Customer/Customer Service Skills Required*<br><br>Key Selling Points<br>$1,200 weekly true up	<br><br>		<br>					*Tenured staff to support you*<br>Home Weekly			<br><br>FAQ																									<br>Are 28’ pups more dangerous than 53’ trailers?																					<br>Negative on the contrary that we have one of the best accidents per million mile in the company. We provide a 3 day class (paid at $150 per day) to ensure you are comfortable with coupling/uncoupling, moving the dolly 							<br>What States do I deliver to																							<br>All 48. However, we rarely go to NY. This is a customer planned account. FXG sends over preplanned week long lanes for each truck. USXD Ops does not adjust the lanes. 											<br>How much money will I make?																							<br>Avg of $1500 weekly @ 2400 mi weekly. 																						<br>																									<br>When is my home time and 34 hour reset?																						<br>We have dispatches 7 days per week for the weekly lane. Reset can fall on any day of the week. If you live within 200 mi of your domicile, you can be home weekly for resets. 											<br>What shift will I work?																							<br>Shifts vary. Indianpolis is evening driving and Ellenwood can vary. 																				<br>When can I take a Vacation?																							<br>After 1 year you will get 1 weeks vacation and after 2 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 7 years, 3 weeks. This totals up to 4 weeks at 10 years!												<br>What kind of truck will I get?																							<br>Our fleet is comprised of Internationals (generally reserved for solos and Freightliners (generally reserved for teams). Each truck must be equipped with a Pintle hook to couple and uncouple the pups. This is done during doubles training class and provided by the shop. 			<br>What is a True-Up? How do I qualify for the True-Up? 																					<br>Work as directed, be on-time, and be available 6 days out of the week for weekly lane dispatch. True up is in place to protect your salary should there be any delays at shipper, breakdowns, or weather delays. This trumps layover pay as well. Our minimum weekly pay is $1700 a long as above conditions are met!<br><br>• Solos on this account will run all 48 states<br>• home for their 34 hours reset weekly.<br>• The weekly minimum is available for Solos who are available to roll 6 days during the week.<br>• Average miles per wk 2250<br>• Solos can expect to make between 57K and 85K per year depending on experience.<br>•The account requires Double endorsement. We will provide 3 days of Doubles training in Irving Shippensburg, or Ellenwood. The training pay will consist of $150 per day<br><br>• Payscale Based On Verified Experience<br>3 -24 Months: 60 CPM<br>2 - 4 Years: 62 CPM<br>4 - 6 Years: 64 CPM<br>6 Years +: 66 CPM<br><br><br>• Weekly Minimum (requires team to be available for 6 days during the week):<br>6 -24 Months: $1100<br>2 - 4 Years: $1200<br>4 - 6 Years: $1300<br>6 Years +: $1400<br><br>• TAGGING<br>JOB: Dedicated OTR DRIVER DLC<br>Solo or Team: Solo<br>Area: OTR<br>Account: Dedicated<br>Dedicated or Domicile Terminal: FedEx Ground]]></description>
