      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[CLOSED Target Lugoff--Need to live within 100 miles of Lugoff, SC. Must have 6 months experience in the last 3 years. LP'S DO NOT RECEIVE ORIENTATION PAY.]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[Key Facts<br>*Patience with Customer/Customer Service Skills Required*<br>*Night and early morning Driving<br>**Weekend and Holiday driving required*<br>*Average $2750 weekly gross<br><br><br>Key Selling Points<br>*Drop and Hook freight<br>*Tenured staff to support you*<br><br><br>FAQ<br>* How hard is the driver unload?<br>No driver touch – all freight unloaded by customer.<br>* What States do I deliver to<br>VA, NC, SC, GA<br>* When is my home time and 34 hour reset?<br>If you are in the area of your home – you can take the truck home as long as there is a safe place to park the truck. Dispatch will make sure you are home for reset if you choose.<br>* What shift will I work?<br>Target ships freight days, nights, weekends, and holidays.<br><br><br><br>If you live within 100 miles of Lugoff, SC, you could be the perfect dedicated driver to add to our Target team! Some of the best parts of being a dedicated driver are getting home WEEKLY, and driving an average of 2,100-2,500 per week..<br><br>As part of the target dedicated team, you’ll run DRY, NO-TOUCH freight to various TARGET locations in SC, GA, VA, NC – all within 600 miles of the LUGOFF distribution center. ALL FREIGHT IS ON PRELOADED TRAILERS AND WILL BE A DROP/HOOK UNLOAD.<br><br>To give you the best possible driving experience, the distribution center includes 24/7 on-site staff, including safety support and a U.S. Xpress shop WITHIN 100 MILES.<br><br>Runs will include nights, weekends, and holidays that fall within your workweek. Routes also typically require 1-2 stops per DAY and potentially a [10]-hour break on the road each week.<br><br>But being a dedicated driver is no easy task. So, the way we see it, you deserve vacation time more than anyone. That’s why after 1 year you will get 1 week vacation and after 2 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 7 years, 3 weeks. This totals up to 4 weeks at 10 years!<br><br>If you choose to join the team, you’ll go through a short orientation to help get you started on the right foot. And you’ll get paid to do it. You’ll attend one day of in-classroom training in which you’ll receive $100, and 1-2 days of ride-along training at $100 per day.<br><br>Pay breakdown<br>1.02 per mile<br><br><br><br>• Tagging<br>IC Job: First Seat Driver<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: Regional<br>Account: Dedicated<br>Dedicated or Domicile Terminal: Target Lugoff]]></description>
