      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED TARGET MADISON, AL- 3 MOS EXP REQ. LIVE WITHIN 75 MILES OF Madison AL. 
Home weekly. Occasionally home daily but not guaranteed. $3k sign-on bonus. 
</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Key Facts<br>*Weekend and Holiday Work<br>*Night Driving*<br>*Double Drop & Hook at Stores”<br><br>Key Selling Points<br>*Home Most Days almost Daily<br>*No-Touch Freight<br><br>FAQ<br>* How hard is the driver unload?<br>This is a no touch drop & hook account<br>* What States do I deliver to<br>AL,GA,MS,LA,FL,TN<br>* How much money will I make?<br>Drivers who run 2200 miles and 5 number of loads make an average of $1150 weekly<br>When is my home time and 34 hour reset?<br>95% of the time it will be on the weekend but due to HOS or customer needs it could be any day of the week, we do get you home weekly.<br>* What shift will I work?<br>24/7 operation and will be required to work nights and weekends.<br>* When can I take a Vacation?<br>After 1 year you will get 1 weeks vacation and after 2 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 7 years, 3 weeks. This totals up to 4 weeks at 10 years!<br>* What kind of truck will I get?<br>Our fleet is comprised of Internationals, Freightliners and Kenworths<br><br><br>If you live within 75 miles of Madison, AL, you could be the perfect dedicated driver to add to our Target Madison team! Some of the best parts of being a dedicated driver are getting home most days and receiving a $3K sign-on bonus, and driving an average of 2100-2300 per week. That’s around $1050 every week and up to $55K annually. <br> <br>As part of the Target dedicated team, you’ll run DRY NO-TOUCH freight to various Target store locations in AL, GA, MS, LA – all within 400 miles of the Target Madison distribution center.<br><br>Runs will include nights, weekends, and holidays that fall within your workweek. Routes also typically require single stops and double drop & hooks at stores.<br><br>But being a dedicated driver is no easy task. So, the way we see it, you deserve vacation time more than anyone. That’s why after 1 year you will get 1 week vacation and after 2 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 7 years, 3 weeks. This totals up to 4 weeks at 10 years!<br><br>If you choose to join the team, you’ll go through a short orientation to help get you started on the right foot. And you’ll get paid to do it. You’ll attend one day of in-classroom training in which you’ll receive $100, and 1 day of ride-along training at $100 per day.<br><br>• Payscale Based On Verified Experience<br>0-5 $0.44<br>6-11 $0.45<br>12-23 $0.46<br>24-35 $0.47<br>36-47 $0.48<br>48-59 $0.49<br>5+ years $0.50<br><br>Team - $.68<br><br>SOB Payout:<br>1st Load - $500<br>30 Days - $500<br>60 Days - $500<br>90 Days - $500<br>120 Days - $500<br>180 Days - $500<br><br>• Tagging<br>Job: Dedicated OTR Driver - DLC<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: regional<br>Acct: Dedicated<br>Region: All<br>DED/Dom Term: Target Madison AL <br>SIGN ON BONUS: Y/N]]></description>
