      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED Target Denton Regional-- must live within 50 miles of DFW, Austin, San Antonio, or Houston. NEED 2 DRIVERS!</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Key Facts<br>*Pallets collapsing in-transit*<br>*Patience with Customer/Customer Service Skills Required*<br>*Not home daily or every weekend*<br><br>Key Selling Points<br>*Pay Package for the area is industry-leading*<br>*Drivers who run 2300 miles and 4 loads make an average of $1400 weekly*<br>*Tenured staff to support you*<br>*3 Different Home-time options*<br><br>FAQ<br>What States do I deliver to<br>Texas<br>How much money will I make?<br>Drivers who run 2300 miles and 4 number of loads make an average of $1400 weekly<br>When is my home time and 34-hour reset?<br>There are 3 different home-time schedules: 6 days on 1 day off, 12 days on 2 days off, 25 days on 3 days off. Office staff will ensure you get home for 34-hour resets.<br>What shift will I work?<br>With most Target deliveries starting in the early AM you will be picking up your loads in the middle of the night and making deliveries the next morning.<br>When can I take a Vacation?<br>After 1 year you will get 1 week of vacation and after 2 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 7 years, 3 weeks. This totals up to 4 weeks at 10 years!<br>What kind of truck will I get?<br>Our fleet is comprised of Internationals, Freightliners and Kenworth tractors.<br> <br><br><br>If you live within 50 miles of Dallas/Fort Worth, Austin, San Antonio, or Houston, Texas, you could be the perfect dedicated driver to add to our Target Denton team! Some of the best parts of being a dedicated driver are getting home Daily/Weekly, depending on which position(s) are open, and driving an average of 2300 miles per week as a regional driver. That’s around $1400 every week and up to $73,000 annually. In addition to mileage pay, you’ll earn $17.50 per stop, after the first stop, as a solo driver.<br> <br>As part of the Target Denton dedicated team, you’ll run refrigerated no-touch freight to Target Stores locations in Texas– all within 500 miles of the Target Denton distribution center. 100% of freight will be live unloaded at Target stores.<br><br>To give you the best possible driving experience, the distribution center includes 24/7 on-site staff, including safety support and a U.S. Xpress shop. <br><br>Runs will include nights, weekends, and holidays that fall within your workweek. Routes also typically require 1-5 stops per day, and potentially a 10-hour break on the road each week. <br><br>But being a dedicated driver is no easy task. So, the way we see it, you deserve vacation time more than anyone. That’s why after a year on the account, you can take a week of paid vacation. After 3 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 7 years, 3 weeks.<br><br>If you choose to join the team, you’ll go through a short orientation to help get you started on the right foot. And you’ll get paid to do it. You’ll attend one day of in-classroom training in which you’ll receive $100, and 1 day of ride-along training at $100 per day.<br><br>PAYSCALE<br>3-11 months .57<br>12-23 months .58<br>24-35 months .59<br>36+ months .60<br>$17.50 per stop after 1st stop<br>If the miles on the route*CPM does not equal more than $100, they automatically make $100 flat rate for the route.<br><br>Tagging:<br>Job: Dedicated OTR Driver - DLC<br>Solo/Team: solo<br>Area: Regional<br>Acct: Dedicated<br>Region: All<br>DED/Dom Term: Target Denton, TX<br>PST/EFA: Required]]></description>
