      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED CAT (Caterpillar) Pomona, MO. HOME WEEKLY! 3 mos experience required. Must Live within 50 miles of Pine Bluff AR; Pomona, MO; Mossville, IL. NEED 1 DRIVER! Email driver placement if you book a driver for this position.</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Risks<br>*Refrigerated trailers*<br>*Patience with Customer/Customer Service Skills Required*<br>*Not home daily*<br>*Terrain/ice and snow in the winter* <br><br>Key Selling Points<br>*Structured routes*<br>*No touch*<br>*Home Weekly*<br>*Average of $1,104-1,512 weekly pending cpm rate*<br>*Tenured staff to support you*<br><br>FAQ<br>What States do I deliver to?<br>IL, MS, AR <br>How much money will I make?<br>Drivers who run the full week averaging 2,200-2,800 miles and 4-5 loads can make an average of $1,104-1,512 weekly pending cpm rate <br>When is my home time and 34 hour reset?<br>95% of the time it will be Friday evening until Sunday evening depending on where you live and when you complete Friday’s load <br>What shift will I work?<br>Mostly 08:00-22:00 <br>When can I take a Vacation?<br>After 1 year you will get 1 weeks vacation and after 2 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 7 years, 3 weeks. This totals up to 4 weeks at 10 years!<br>What kind of truck will I get?<br>Our fleet is comprised of Internationals, Freightliners and Kenworth’s<br><br>Based out of Pomona, MO<br>• Regional, Home Weekly for 34 Reset.<br>• Touch Freight: No<br>• Average Weekly Pay: $1,104<br>• Top Weekly Pay: $1,512<br>• Pay Type: CPM<br>• Sign-on-Bonus: No<br><br>If you live within 50 miles of Pomona, MO, Mossville, IL or Pine Bluff, AR, you could be the perfect Dedicated driver to add to our Caterpillar team! Some of the best parts of being a Dedicated driver are getting home weekly, and driving an average of 2,200-2,800 miles per week. That’s around $1,104-1,512 every week for mileage and up to $58-79K annually. <br> <br>As part of the Caterpillar Dedicated team, you’ll run refrigerated (rubber) freight to various Caterpillar DC’s located in IL, MS, and AR – all within 200-370 miles of the distribution center in Pomona, MO. 50% of freight will be live loaded and 50% will be drop and hook at the Caterpillar DC’s.<br><br>To give you the best possible driving experience, you can count on USX off-site staff 24/7, including on call safety support and a U.S. Xpress maintenance shop within 215 miles of the DC. <br><br>Runs will include nights, partial weekends, and possibly holidays that fall within your workweek. Routes also typically require 1 stop per day, 4-5 refrigerated trailers per week and a daily 10 hour break on the road each week. <br><br>Being a Dedicated driver is no easy task. So, the way we see it, you deserve vacation time more than anyone. That’s why after a year on the account, you can take a week of paid vacation. After 2 years, you can take 2 weeks of vacation. And after 7 years, 3 weeks.<br><br>If you choose to join the team, you’ll go through a short orientation remotely to get you on the best track to success! <br><br><br>• Payscale Based On Verified Experience<br>•0 Month-23 Months .46<br>•24 Months .48<br>•48 Months .49<br>•72 Months .50<br>•96 Months .52<br>•120 Months .54<br><br>• This account offers a paid vacation of 1 week after 1 year, 2 weeks after 2 years, 3 weeks after 7 years and 4 weeks after 10 years.<br><br>• Tagging<br>Job: Dedicated OTR Driver - DLC<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: OTR<br>Acct: Dedicated<br>Region: All<br>DED/Dom Term: Caterpillar Pomona MO (CMO)<br>SIGN ON BONUS: Y/N]]></description>
