      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[CLOSED YRC/FXG Team 200 miles of Dallas, TX. LEASE HOME WEEKLY! Must have 6 months experience in the last 3 years. LP'S DO NOT RECEIVE ORIENTATION PAY.
]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[Account key selling points<br>• Teams on this account can get home every week for a 34 hour reset, but they can stay out longer if they would like.<br>• 5500 (miles) x $1.25 = $6875/week to the truck + fuel surcharge.<br>• Drivers run 48 states but there will be set routes within the DC's<br>• Truck owner will need to pay his team partner (employee) out of the money.<br>• Annually $328,900 (Very top end)<br>• The account requires Double endorsement.<br><br>Additional account details<br>• Average 5000-5500 miles per week<br>• Loads are Drop and Hook. Drivers will not be breaking down the doubles.<br>• If a team does not have their endorsements when they are hired: operations will expect team to get doubles endorsement as soon as possible, and they will work with the team to get certifications within the first 30 days, (10-12 question quiz at the DMV) in the meantime a team w/o endorsements will be running other various general OTR or dedicated FAK freight.<br>• We will provide 3 days of Doubles training @ $150 per day<br>• Ellenwood- Monday & Wednesday<br>• Shippensburg- Wednesday<br>• Irving- Friday<br><br>Pay breakdown<br>• IC/LP Drivers<br>$1.25 per mile + fuel surcharge (empty and loaded miles)<br><br>• Tagging<br>IC Job: First Seat Driver<br>Solo/Team: Team<br>Area: OTR<br>Acct: Dedicated<br>Region: All<br>DED/Dom Term: FXG Dedicated Tour<br>Ded Tour: FXG]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-503-DB4436</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -97.4678606,32.6837588,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED CH ROBINSON-LEASE</name>
        <description><![CDATA[While your customer is CH Robinson, you will not have to deal with them at all, only with the US Xpress team. You’ll haul general commodities (basically anything and everything, but no hazmat) with no touch, live load/live unload freight in a loop which runs primarily between the Dallas, Chicago, and Atlanta areas, including some runs out west (ND/SD/WY/UT/NM/NV/CA/WA/OR, etc). You will run very little freight into the northeast. Drivers need to expect to be out for 2 weeks and get 2 days home. You get a weekend reset (not at home, but it does give you a break over the weekend). With having the weekends to reset, it’s a great way to enjoy parts of the country you may not otherwise see.<br><br>Pay Info<br>• $1.15 per mile<br><br>• Tagging<br>IC Job: First Seat Driver<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: OTR<br>Acct: Dedicated<br>Region: All <br>Dedicated Tour Acct: CH Robinson Tour<br>DED/Dom Term: Home Terminal                              Updated : 6.25.21]]></description>
