      <Placemark>
        <name>CLOSED Recovery Driver</name>
        <description><![CDATA[• Flat daily rate with additional pay<br>• Must live within 50 miles of major airport and be comfortable with flying regularly<br>• Average Weekly pay $1235<br><br>Job Description<br>• Will Require overnight trips<br>• Recover company equipment from various locations & will Return Equipment to Service Center.<br>• May Drive shuttle van around local area and bring drivers to retrieve equipment or on work related errands.<br>• Operate a tractor trailer over the roads, highways and interstates. Obey all traffic laws and drive with caution while operating the motor vehicle.<br>• Immediately report damage or other claim issues that arise to customers or rail yards while on site and then to USX Claims Department. Immediately report any damage to tractors, trailers or third parties to the USX Claims Department.<br>• Road test vehicles that have been repaired in the shops, or vehicles that may require repair.<br>• May conduct road examinations with student drivers<br>• Must have vision to see clearly during night time hours.<br>• Maintain a clean and neat physical appearance.<br>• Maintain a clean vehicle.<br>• May include other duties as assigned by Management.<br>• May drive equipment to dealer for dealer/warranty repairs<br>• May be asked to help with moving equipment around the yard for maintenance department.<br><br>Pay Scale<br>$148.57 per day in addition to:<br>$25 for a recovery less than 250 miles away<br>$40 recovery 251-480 miles away<br>$55 recovery 481-600 miles away<br>$75 for recovery 601+ miles away<br><br> <br>• TAGGING<br>Job: First Seat Driver<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: Local<br>Acct: all accounts]]></description>
