          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[CLOSED DG MARION, IN -  Average $100k-$170k per year! Average of $1.20-$1.40 cpm ($0.55-$0.65 mileage + $200 unload + $30 stop) New hire training pay and ride along time ($150 per load and 5 days with driver) 
New Hires will be sent directly to DG Marion if hired from Monday's class. Wednesday's orientation class must report the following Monday after hire.
]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[•	Regional, Home weekly for 34 Reset<br>•	Touch Freight: Yes, using rolltainers with topper freight<br>•	Average Weekly Pay: $1,992<br>•	Top Weekly Pay Potential: $2900 <br>•	$1800.00 True Up  after training if all requirements are met.<br>•	Pay Type: Mileage / Trailer / Stop <br><br><br>You could be the perfect Dedicated driver to add to our Dollar General Marion Team! Some of the best parts of being a Dedicated driver are getting home weekly and driving an average of 1,500 miles per week 5 trailers per week and average 15 stops or more. That’s around [$1,992] earning potential every week or more with a true up of $1,800 as long as drivers meet certain criteria, and up to $102,000 annually. In addition to mileage pay, you’ll earn $200 per outbound load inclusive for the unload and all stops pay at $30. <br> <br>As part of the Dollar General Dedicated team, you’ll run DRY / TOUCH freight to various Dollar General locations in [OH,IN, MI, and IL – all within 300 miles of the distribution center in [Marion, IN]. [100%] of freight will be live unloaded at Dollar General stores.<br><br>To give you the best possible driving experience, the distribution center includes 24/7 staff, including safety support and a U.S. Xpress maintenance contact. <br><br>This account with Dollar General is unique. It’s hard work, but Dollar General provides the tools and support you need, including rolltainers and u-boats. The good news is that you control the pace of unloading. You won’t have to wait on someone else to arrive and unload. Unloading your truck lets you get those steps and a light workout in on the job, too. [Send video of unload process to driver: https://vimeo.com/646033145/ef84bb525c].<br><br>Runs will include nights, weekends, and holidays that fall within your workweek. Routes also typically require [3-6] stops per [DAY], and a [34] hour break at home every week. Drivers that wish to stay out for more than a week can be worked with to increase their earning potential.<br><br>Being a Dedicated driver is no easy task. So, the way we see it, you deserve vacation time more than anyone. That’s why after a year on the account, you can take a week of paid vacation. After [2] years, you can take [2] weeks of vacation. And after [7] years 3 weeks, [10] years 4 weeks.<br><br>If you choose to join the team, you’ll go through a short orientation to help get you started on the right foot. And you’ll get paid to do it. You’ll attend one day of in-classroom training in which you’ll receive [$150], and then you’ll complete [3-5] days of ride-along training at [$150] per day with an experienced driver.<br><br>• Payscale Based On Verified Experience<br><br>0 Months $0.55<br>1 year $0.56<br>2 years $0.57<br>3 years $0.58<br>4 years $0.59<br>5 years $0.60<br>6 years $0.61<br>7 years $0.62<br>8 years $0.63<br>9 years $0.64<br>10 years $0.65<br><br><br>• Unload Pay $200 per outbound trailer (4-6 loads per week)<br>• Stop Pay $30.00<br>• $1800 weekly True Up if requirements are met<br><br><br>• Tagging<br>Job: Dedicated OTR Driver - DLC<br>Solo/Team: Solo<br>Area: Regional<br>Acct: Dedicated<br>Region: All<br>DED/Dom Term: DG Marion, IN<br>PST: Required<br>SIGN ON BONUS: Y/N Yes]]></description>
